RuathlekSecret LanguageFamily: Ulou ( a la Baltic: Old Prussian, Lettish, Lithuanian )SubGroup: NethereseAlphabet: DraconicRegions Spoken: Nimbral, Illusionist libraries and GuildsDificulty: 4Ruathlek is the secret language of illusionists. It is said this language was developed by the now dead goddess of deception and illusion Leira, for use by worshippers and illusionists, and the wizards of Nimbral. It was largely based on Netherese.While generally a language used for magical research, the people of Nimbral use it in their every day lives in addition to magical endeavers.Waterdeep is known to hold at least one library of books in this dweomer guarded tongue.